{"parse":{"title":"How to Be a Jewish Mother","pageid":36864214,"revid":795142533,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\">How to Be a Jewish Mother, a very lovely training manual <span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=How+to+Be+a+Jewish+Mother%2C+a+very+lovely+training+manual&amp;rft.author=%5B%5BDan+Greenburg%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=October+1964&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BPrice+Stern+Sloan%5D%5D&amp;rft.pages=99\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:HowToBeAJewishMother.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"HowToBeAJewishMother.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/c/cb/HowToBeAJewishMother.jpg\" width=\"195\" height=\"220\" data-file-width=\"195\" data-file-height=\"220\" /></a><div>First edition</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Dan_Greenburg\" title=\"Dan Greenburg\">Dan Greenburg</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country</th><td>\nUnited States</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language</th><td>\nEnglish</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Publisher</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Price_Stern_Sloan\" title=\"Price Stern Sloan\">Price Stern Sloan</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Publication date</div></th><td>\nOctober 1964<sup id=\"cite_ref-suss1_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-suss1-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Media&#160;type</th><td>\nPrint (<a href=\"/wiki/Hardcover\" title=\"Hardcover\">Hardcover</a>)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Pages</th><td>\n99</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>How to Be a Jewish Mother</b></i> is a 1964 <a href=\"/wiki/Jewish_humour\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Jewish humour\">Jewish humour</a> book by American <a href=\"/wiki/Humorist\" title=\"Humorist\">humorist</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Dan_Greenburg\" title=\"Dan Greenburg\">Dan Greenburg</a> which was the best selling non-fiction book in the United States in 1965, with 270,000 copies sold.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ref1_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ref1-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-books_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-books-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-maaaa_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-maaaa-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> The book was first published by <a href=\"/wiki/Price_Stern_Sloan\" title=\"Price Stern Sloan\">Price Stern Sloan</a> under publisher <a href=\"/wiki/Larry_Sloan\" title=\"Larry Sloan\">Larry Sloan</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-pw_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-pw-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-time_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-time-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The book was adapted into a play starring <a href=\"/wiki/Molly_Picon\" title=\"Molly Picon\">Molly Picon</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Godfrey_Cambridge\" title=\"Godfrey Cambridge\">Godfrey Cambridge</a> which had a brief run on <a href=\"/wiki/Broadway_theatre\" title=\"Broadway theatre\">Broadway</a> at the <a href=\"/wiki/Hudson_Theater\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hudson Theater\">Hudson Theater</a> from December 1967 through January 1968.<sup id=\"cite_ref-suss1_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-suss1-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-play1_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-play1-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>The play was profiled in the <a href=\"/wiki/William_Goldman\" title=\"William Goldman\">William Goldman</a> book <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Season:_A_Candid_Look_at_Broadway\" title=\"The Season: A Candid Look at Broadway\">The Season: A Candid Look at Broadway</a></i>.\n</p><p>A 1983 French adaptation, <i>Comment devenir une m\u00e8re juive en 10 le\u00e7ons</i>, met with long-running success.<sup id=\"cite_ref-france1_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-france1-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-french2_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-french2-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>  <a href=\"/wiki/Gertrude_Berg\" title=\"Gertrude Berg\">Gertrude Berg</a> also released a best-selling comedy album from the book in 1965.<sup id=\"cite_ref-suss1_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-suss1-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=How_to_Be_a_Jewish_Mother&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-suss1-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-suss1_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-suss1_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-suss1_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Battaglio, Stephen. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=E1TT4POdbGUC&amp;pg=PA251&amp;lpg=PA251&amp;dq=%22how+to+be+a+jewish+mother%22+greenburg+1964&amp;source=bl&amp;ots=Bg6JubtWVT&amp;sig=aOio-ebd2GYmYVzxv4PMwDoTr-E&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;ei=i2Y-UK6FLOyI6AHs7YD4Bg&amp;ved=0CEAQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&amp;q=%22how%20to%20be%20a%20jewish%20mother%22%20greenburg%201964&amp;f=false\">David Susskind: A Televised Life</a>, p. 251 (2010)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-ref1-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-ref1_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Hackett, Alice Payne. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=cOI8AQAAIAAJ\">Seventy years of best sellers, 1895-1965</a>, p. 227 (1967)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-books-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-books_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?ei=-WM-UJDbGsm16AHJ7oGIDw&amp;id=s-5OAAAAIAAJ&amp;dq=\">The Bookseller</a> (\"Non-Fiction. The bestseller of the year in non- fiction was a book called How to Be a Jewish Mother, by Dan Greenburg\")</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-maaaa-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-maaaa_4-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Bernstein, Fred A. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=zPl2wNG0EDwC&amp;pg=PT23#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false\">The Jewish Mothers' Hall of Fame</a> (chapter on Leah Greenburg and the book) (1986)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-pw-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-pw_5-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Werris, Wendy (2012-10-15). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/authors/obituaries/article/54394-obituary-larry-sloan-89.html\">\"Obituary: Larry Sloan, 89\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Publishers_Weekly\" title=\"Publishers Weekly\">Publishers Weekly</a></i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2012-11-17</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Publishers+Weekly&amp;rft.atitle=Obituary%3A+Larry+Sloan%2C+89&amp;rft.date=2012-10-15&amp;rft.aulast=Werris&amp;rft.aufirst=Wendy&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.publishersweekly.com%2Fpw%2Fby-topic%2Fauthors%2Fobituaries%2Farticle%2F54394-obituary-larry-sloan-89.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHow+to+Be+a+Jewish+Mother\" class=\"Z3988\"><span